Abstract = {Hyperspectral images (HSIs) provide detailed spectral information
   through hundreds of (narrow) spectral channels (also known as
   dimensionality or bands), which can be used to accurately classify
   diverse materials of interest. The increased dimensionality of such data
   makes it possible to significantly improve data information content but
   provides a challenge to conventional techniques (the so-called curse of
   dimensionality) for accurate analysis of HSIs.},
